This paper deals with the problem of allocating indivisible items to agents with additive utilities, which is a classic problem in computational social choice. The problem involves both game theory and algorithms, making cs.GT and cs.DS the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which is a common topic in cs.AI and cs.LG. Finally, the problem of allocating resources is a fundamental topic in cs.EC, which makes it a likely sub-category as well.
